# sfOAuthPlugin #

If you want to use OAuth with many services out of box, you can use [sfMelodyPlugin](http://www.symfony-project.org/plugins/sfMelodyPlugin "sfMelodyPlugin").

To store tokens with Doctrine, you can use [sfDoctrineOAuthPlugin](http://www.symfony-project.org/plugins/sfDoctrineOAuthPlugin "sfDoctrineOAuthPlugin").

To store tokens with Propel, you can use [sfPropelOAuthPlugin](http://www.symfony-project.org/plugins/sfPropelOAuthPlugin "sfPropelOAuthPlugin"). (coming soon)

It's an implementation of OAuth version 1 and 2 for easy using with symfony.

Feel free to contribute on github : [sfOAuthPlugin](http://github.com/chok/sfOAuthPlugin "sfOAuthPlugin")

